  <body> <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode">🌙 Dark Mode</button>
    <p><br>
    </p>
    <div>
      <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: EYE IRRITATION / ITCHING</h3>
      <!-- S: Site -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Site
          &amp; Laterality</span> <span class="verbal">"Which eye is bothering
          you? Is it one or both? Is the feeling on the eyeball itself, or more
          on the eyelids?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>UNILATERAL (One Eye)
            <ul>
              <li class="ophthalmology">Foreign body, </li>
              <li class="ophthalmology">Blocked tear duct, </li>
              <li class="ophthalmology"><b class="cns">Herpes Zoster</b></li>
              <li class="ophthalmology">Episcleritis</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>BILATERAL (Both Eyes)
            <ul>
              <li class="ophthalmology">Allergic or Viral Conjunctivitis</li>
              <li class="ophthalmology">Dry Eye Disease, Blepharitis</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- O: Onset -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>: Onset</span>
        <span class="verbal">"When did you first notice this? Did it come on
          suddenly or gradually over time?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>SUDDEN: <span class="ophthalmology">Allergy, Foreign Body,
              Chemical Splash, <b class="emergency">Subconjunctival Hemorrhage
                (after strain/trauma)</b></span></li>
          <li>GRADUAL: <span class="ophthalmology">Dry Eye, Blepharitis,
              Viral/Bacterial Conjunctivitis</span></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- D: Duration -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>: Duration</span>
        <span class="verbal">"How long has this been going on? Is it constant or
          does it come and go?"</span> </li>
      <!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>:
          Aggravating &amp; Relieving Factors</span> <span class="verbal">"What
          makes it feel worse? Screens, wind, bright lights? What helps? Drops,
          rest?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li><em>AGGRAVATING</em>: </li>
          <li class="ophthalmology"><b><u>Contact lenses</u></b></li>
          <li class="ophthalmology"><b><u>eye drops<br>
              </u></b></li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Screen use/reading, wind, A/C (Dry Eye); </li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Bright light (Photophobia); </li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Known allergens (pollen, pets).</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">exposure to chemicals</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">trauma</li>
          <li><b>RELIEVING</b>: </li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Artificial tears/lubricating drops; </li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Antihistamine drops; </li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Cool compresses; </li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Resting eyes.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- C: Character (THE KEY DIFFERENTIATOR) -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>:
          Character of Discomfort</span> <span class="verbal">"Can you describe
          the feeling? Is it mainly itchy, gritty, burning, or more of a
          soreness?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>ITCHING (Pruritus): <b class="ophthalmology">Hallmark of Allergic
              Conjunctivitis</b>.</li>
          <li>GRITTY / SANDY / FOREIGN BODY SENSATION: <b class="ophthalmology">Classic
              for Dry Eye or Viral Conjunctivitis</b>.</li>
          <li>BURNING: <b class="ophthalmology">Common in Dry Eye and
              Blepharitis (eyelid inflammation)</b>.</li>
          <li>SORENESS / DULL ACHE: <b class="ophthalmology">Episcleritis,
              Scleritis</b>.</li>
          <li>STICKINESS / MATTING OF LIDS (esp. on waking): <b class="ophthalmology infectious">Classic
              for Bacterial Conjunctivitis</b>.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- R: Radiation (of Pain) -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
          Radiation</span> <span class="verbal">"Is there any pain that spreads
          from the eye, for example, a headache?"</span> </li>
      <!-- A: Associated Symptoms -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>:
          Associated Symptoms</span> <span class="verbal">"Besides the
          irritation, have you noticed any discharge, redness, or changes in
          your vision?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>DISCHARGE
            <ul>
              <li class="ophthalmology">Watery / Tearing (Epiphora): <b class="infectious">Viral</b>,
                <b class="rheumatic">Allergic</b>, <b class="ophthalmology">Dry
                  Eye (reflex tearing)</b></li>
              <li class="ophthalmology">Stringy, white mucoid: <b class="rheumatic">Allergic</b></li>
              <li class="ophthalmology infectious">Purulent (pus, yellow/green):
                <b class="infectious">Bacterial</b></li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>VISUAL CHANGES
            <ul>
              <li class="ophthalmology">Blurred vision that clears with
                blinking? (Suggests tear film/discharge issue)</li>
              <li class="ophthalmology emergency">Constant blurred vision? Halos
                around lights? (Red Flags)</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>APPEARANCE
            <ul>
              <li class="ophthalmology">Redness (diffuse or in one sector?), Lid
                swelling, Crusting on lashes</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>SYSTEMIC SYMPTOMS
            <ul>
              <li class="infectious">Fever, cough, runny nose? (Viral prodrome)</li>
              <li class="rheumatic">Sneezing, nasal congestion? (Allergies)</li>
              <li class="rheumatic">Joint pain, dry mouth? (Autoimmune, e.g.,
                Sjogren's)</li>
              <li class="emergency cns">Nausea / Vomiting? (Glaucoma red flag)</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Shingles<br>
            <ul>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- P: Progression -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
          Progression</span> <span class="verbal">"Since it started, has the
          issue gotten better, worse, or stayed about the same?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>Very Rapid = Inflammatory</li>
          <li>Slowly = Benign process (e.g., pterygium)</li>
          <li>Static -&gt; Rapid = Suggests change in a chronic condition</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- P: Pattern -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Pattern</span>
        <span class="verbal">"Is it worse at a particular time of day, like in
          the morning or at the end of the day?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>Worse in the morning (lids matted shut): <b class="infectious">Bacterial
              Conjunctivitis</b></li>
          <li>Worse as the day progresses (after screen use/reading): <b class="ophthalmology">Dry
              Eye Disease</b></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- E: Effect on life -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>: Effect
          on Life</span> <span class="verbal">"How is this affecting your daily
          activities like reading, driving, or work? Does it interfere with
          movement?"</span> </li>
      <!-- R: Red Flags -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Red
          Flags</span> <span class="verbal">"I must ask some specific questions
          to make sure we're not missing anything more serious."</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="emergency ophthalmology">SEVERE PAIN</li>
          <li class="emergency ophthalmology">SIGNIFICANT VISION LOSS (not
            cleared by blinking)</li>
          <li class="emergency ophthalmology">PHOTOPHOBIA (severe light
            sensitivity)</li>
          <li class="emergency cns">HALOS AROUND LIGHTS, NAUSEA/VOMITING (Acute
            Glaucoma)</li>
          <li class="emergency ophthalmology">CHEMICAL SPLASH / PENETRATING
            TRAUMA</li>
          <li class="emergency cns">ABNORMAL PUPIL SHAPE OR SIZE</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- S: Severity -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Severity
          / Bother Scale</span> <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10,
          how bothersome is this irritation?"</span> </li>
    </div>
    <br>
    <br>
    <br>
    <br>
    <br>
    <br>
